<item>
            <title>[SPARK-18726] Filesystem unnecessarily scanned twice during creation of non-catalog table</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-18726</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It seems that for non-catalog tables (e.g. spark.read.parquet(...)), we scan the filesystem twice, once for schema inference, and another to create a FileIndex class for the relation.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It would be better to combine these scans somehow, since this is the most costly step of creating a table. This is a follow-up ticket to &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/16090&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/16090&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;cc &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=cloud_fan&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;cloud_fan&quot;&gt;cloud_fan&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
